20that%20performs%20at%20a%20similar%20level%20to%20OpenAI's%20GPT-4o%20and%20Anthropic's%20Claude%203.5.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20these%20models%20are%20prone%20to%20errors%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fabs%2F2401.08358%5C%22%3Esometimes%20make%20up%20their%20own%20facts%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20they%20can%20carry%20out%20tasks%20such%20as%20answering%20questions%2C%20writing%20essays%20and%20generating%20computer%20code.%20On%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.anthropic.com%2Fnews%2Fclaude-3-family%5C%22%3Esome%20tests%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20problem-solving%20and%20mathematical%20reasoning%2C%20they%20score%20better%20than%20the%20average%20human.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EV3%20was%20trained%20at%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scmp.com%2Ftech%2Ftech-trends%2Farticle%2F3293050%2Fmeet-deepseek-chinese-start-changing-how-ai-models-are-trained%5C%22%3Ereported%20cost%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20about%20US%245.58%20million.%20This%20is%20dramatically%20cheaper%20than%20GPT-4%2C%20for%20example%2C%20which%20cost%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fstory%2Fopenai-ceo-sam-altman-the-age-of-giant-ai-models-is-already-over%2F%5C%22%3Emore%20than%20US%24100%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20develop.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeepSeek%20also%20claims%20to%20have%20trained%20V3%20using%20around%202%2C000%20specialised%20computer%20chips%2C%20specifically%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Ftechnology%2Fnvidia-says-deepseek-advances-prove-need-more-its-chips-2025-01-27%2F%5C%22%3EH800%20GPUs%20made%20by%20NVIDIA%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20is%20again%20much%20fewer%20than%20other%20companies%2C%20which%20may%20have%20used%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2025%2F01%2F23%2Ftechnology%2Fdeepseek-china-ai-chips.html%5C%22%3Eup%20to%2016%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20more%20powerful%20H100%20chips.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20January%2020%2C%20DeepSeek%20released%20another%20model%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fabs%2F2501.12948%5C%22%3Ecalled%20R1%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20is%20a%20so-called%20%E2%80%9Creasoning%E2%80%9D%20model%2C%20which%20tries%20to%20work%20through%20complex%20problems%20step%20by%20step.%20These%20models%20seem%20to%20be%20better%20at%20many%20tasks%20that%20require%20context%20and%20have%20multiple%20interrelated%20parts%2C%20such%20as%20reading%20comprehension%20and%20strategic%20planning.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20R1%20model%20is%20a%20tweaked%20version%20of%20V3%2C%20modified%20with%20a%20technique%20called%20reinforcement%20learning.%20R1%20appears%20to%20work%20at%20a%20similar%20level%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopenai.com%2Fo1%2F%5C%22%3EOpenAI's%20o1%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20released%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeepSeek%20also%20used%20the%20same%20technique%20to%20make%20%E2%80%9Creasoning%E2%80%9D%20versions%20of%20small%20open-source%20models%20that%20can%20run%20on%20home%20computers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20release%20has%20sparked%20a%20huge%20surge%20of%20interest%20in%20DeepSeek%2C%20driving%20up%20the%20popularity%20of%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Ftechnology%2F2025%2Fjan%2F27%2Fdeepseek-cyberattack-ai%5C%22%3EV3-powered%20chatbot%20app%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20triggering%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2Fe670a4ea-05ad-4419-b72a-7727e8a6d471%5C%22%3Emassive%20price%20crash%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20tech%20stocks%20as%20investors%20re-evaluate%20the%20AI%20industry.%20At%20the%20time%20of%20writing%2C%20chipmaker%20NVIDIA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abc.net.au%2Fnews%2F2025-01-28%2Fasx-markets-business-news-live-updates%2F104865804%5C%22%3Ehas%20lost%20around%20US%24600%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20value.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EHow%20DeepSeek%20did%20it%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeepSeek's%20breakthroughs%20have%20been%20in%20achieving%20greater%20efficiency%3A%20getting%20good%20results%20with%20fewer%20resources.%20In%20particular%2C%20DeepSeek's%20developers%20have%20pioneered%20two%20techniques%20that%20may%20be%20adopted%20by%20AI%20researchers%20more%20broadly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20has%20to%20do%20with%20a%20mathematical%20idea%20called%20%E2%80%9Csparsity%E2%80%9D.%20AI%20models%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20parameters%20that%20determine%20their%20responses%20to%20inputs%20(V3%20has%20around%20671%20billion)%2C%20but%20only%20a%20small%20fraction%20of%20these%20parameters%20is%20used%20for%20any%20given%20input.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20predicting%20which%20parameters%20will%20be%20needed%20isn't%20easy.%20DeepSeek%20used%20a%20new%20technique%20to%20do%20this%2C%20and%20then%20trained%20only%20those%20parameters.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20its%20models%20needed%20far%20less%20training%20than%20a%20conventional%20approach.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20trick%20has%20to%20do%20with%20how%20V3%20stores%20information%20in%20computer%20memory.%20DeepSeek%20has%20found%20a%20clever%20way%20to%20compress%20the%20relevant%20data%2C%20so%20it%20is%20easier%20to%20store%20and%20access%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EWhat%20it%20means%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeepSeek's%20models%20and%20techniques%20have%20been%20released%20under%20the%20free%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopensource.org%2Flicense%2Fmit%5C%22%3EMIT%20License%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20means%20anyone%20can%20download%20and%20modify%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20this%20may%20be%20bad%20news%20for%20some%20AI%20companies%20%E2%80%93%20whose%20profits%20might%20be%20eroded%20by%20the%20existence%20of%20freely%20available%2C%20powerful%20models%20%E2%80%93%20it%20is%20great%20news%20for%20the%20broader%20AI%20research%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20present%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20AI%20research%20requires%20access%20to%20enormous%20amounts%20of%20computing%20resources.%20Researchers%20like%20myself%20who%20are%20based%20at%20universities%20(or%20anywhere%20except%20large%20tech%20companies)%20have%20had%20limited%20ability%20to%20carry%20out%20tests%20and%20experiments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20efficient%20models%20and%20techniques%20change%20the%20situation.%20Experimentation%20and%20development%20may%20now%20be%20significantly%20easier%20for%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20consumers%2C%20access%20to%20AI%20may%20also%20become%20cheaper.%20More%20AI%20models%20may%20be%20run%20on%20users'%20own%20devices%2C%20such%20as%20laptops%20or%20phones%2C%20rather%20than%20running%20%E2%80%9Cin%20the%20cloud%E2%80%9D%20for%20a%20subscription%20fee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20researchers%20who%20already%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20resources%2C%20more%20efficiency%20may%20have%20less%20of%20an%20effect.%20It%20is%20unclear%20whether%20DeepSeek's%20approach%20will%20help%20to%20make%20models%20with%20better%20performance%20overall%2C%20or%20simply%20models%20that%20are%20more%20efficient.%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22no-referrer-when-downgrade%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F248434%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E(Author%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Ftongliang-liu-2309993%5C%22%3ETongliang%20Liu%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Associate%20Professor%20of%20Machine%20Learning%20and%20Director%20of%20the%20Sydney%20AI%20Centre%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Funiversity-of-sydney-841%5C%22%3EUniversity%20of%20Sydney%3C%2Fa%3E)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Disclosure%20statement%3A%C2%A0Tongliang%20Liu%20does%20not%20work%20for%2C%20consult%2C%20own%20shares%20in%20or%20receive%20funding%20from%20any%20company%20or%20organisation%20that%20would%20benefit%20from%20this%20article%2C%20and%20has%20disclosed%20no%20relevant%20affiliations%20beyond%20their%20academic%20appointment.)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(This%20article%20is%20republished%20from%20%3