0are%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.18653%2Fv1%2FW17-1606%5C%22%3Ewoman%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.48550%2FarXiv.2103.15122%5C%22%3Eold%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20are%20too%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.48550%2FarXiv.2103.15122%5C%22%3Eyoung%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20have%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fdx.doi.org%2F10.21437%2FInterspeech.2019-2993%5C%22%3Espeech%20impediment%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3ETin%20ear%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnlike%20you%20or%20me%2C%20automatic%20speech%20recognition%20systems%20are%20not%20what%20researchers%20call%20%E2%80%9Csympathetic%20listeners.%E2%80%9D%20Instead%20of%20trying%20to%20understand%20you%20by%20taking%20in%20other%20useful%20clues%20like%20intonation%20or%20facial%20gestures%2C%20they%20simply%20give%20up.%20Or%20they%20take%20a%20probabilistic%20guess%2C%20a%20move%20that%20can%20sometimes%20result%20in%20an%20error.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20companies%20and%20public%20agencies%20increasingly%20adopt%20automatic%20speech%20recognition%20tools%20in%20order%20to%20cut%20costs%2C%20people%20have%20little%20choice%20but%20to%20interact%20with%20them.%20But%20the%20more%20that%20these%20systems%20come%20into%20use%20in%20critical%20fields%2C%20ranging%20from%20emergency%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dhs.gov%2Fmedialibrary%2Fassets%2Fvideos%2F23524%5C%22%3Efirst%20responders%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fstory%2Fhospitals-ai-transcription-tools-hallucination%2F%5C%22%3Ehealth%20care%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1080%2F09588221.2022.2080230%5C%22%3Eeducation%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.48550%2FarXiv.2405.13166%5C%22%3Elaw%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1016%2Fj.fsisyn.2024.100563%5C%22%3Eenforcement%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20more%20likely%20there%20will%20be%20grave%20consequences%20when%20they%20fail%20to%20recognize%20what%20people%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImagine%20sometime%20in%20the%20near%20future%20you've%20been%20hurt%20in%20a%20car%20crash.%20You%20dial%20911%20to%20call%20for%20help%2C%20but%20instead%20of%20being%20connected%20to%20a%20human%20dispatcher%2C%20you%20get%20a%20bot%20that's%20designed%20to%20weed%20out%20nonemergency%20calls.%20It%20takes%20you%20several%20rounds%20to%20be%20understood%2C%20wasting%20time%20and%20raising%20your%20anxiety%20level%20at%20the%20worst%20moment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20causes%20this%20kind%20of%20error%20to%20occur%3F%20Some%20of%20the%20inequalities%20that%20result%20from%20these%20systems%20are%20baked%20into%20the%20reams%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1145%2F3442188.3445922%5C%22%3Elinguistic%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20developers%20use%20to%20build%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdirect.mit.edu%2Fcoli%2Farticle%2F50%2F3%2F1097%2F121961%2FBias-and-Fairness-in-Large-Language-Models-A%5C%22%3Elarge%20language%20models%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Developers%20train%20artificial%20intelligence%20systems%20to%20understand%20and%20mimic%20human%20language%20by%20feeding%20them%20vast%20quantities%20of%20text%20and%20audio%20files%20containing%20real%20human%20speech.%20But%20whose%20speech%20are%20they%20feeding%20them%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20system%20scores%20high%20accuracy%20rates%20when%20speaking%20with%20affluent%20white%20Americans%20in%20their%20mid-30s%2C%20it%20is%20reasonable%20to%20guess%20that%20it%20was%20trained%20using%20plenty%20of%20audio%20recordings%20of%20people%20who%20fit%20this%20profile.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20rigorous%20data%20collection%20from%20a%20diverse%20range%20of%20sources%2C%20AI%20developers%20could%20reduce%20these%20errors.%20But%20to%20build%20AI%20systems%20that%20can%20understand%20the%20infinite%20variations%20in%20human%20speech%20arising%20from%20things%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.48550%2FarXiv.2406.09855%5C%22%3Egender%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fulrichboser%2F2024%2F11%2F25%2Fwhy-cant-automatic-speech-recognition-systems-understand-kids%2F%5C%22%3Eage%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.stanford.edu%2Fstories%2F2020%2F03%2Fautomated-speech-recognition-less-accurate-blacks%5C%22%3Erace%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnymag.com%2Fintelligencer%2F2018%2F08%2Fwhy-are-google-siri-and-alexa-so-bad-at-understanding-bilingual-accents-voice-assistants.html%5C%22%3Efirst%20vs.%20second%20language%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.48550%2FarXiv.2403.04445%5C%22%3Esocioeconomic%20status%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1007%2F978-3-031-21707-4_30%5C%22%3Eability%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20plenty%20else%2C%20requires%20significant%20resources%20and%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%E2%80%98Proper'%20English%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20people%20who%20do%20not%20speak%20English%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20to%20say%2C%20most%20people%20around%20the%20world%20%E2%80%93%20the%20challenges%20are%20even%20greater.%20Most%20of%20the%20world's%20largest%20generative%20AI%20systems%20were%20built%20in%20English%2C%20and%20they%20work%20far%20better%20in%20English%20than%20in%20any%20other%20language.%20On%20paper%2C%20AI%20has%20lots%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2F%40askiefer%2Fit-started-with-a-whisper-4090d26d95e4%5C%22%3Ecivic%20potential%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20translation%20and%20increasing%20people's%20access%20to%20information%20in%20different%20languages%2C%20but%20for%20now%2C%20most%20languages%20have%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.mit.edu%2F2021%2Fspeech-recognition-uncommon-languages-1104%5C%22%3Esmaller%20digital%20footprint%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20making%20it%20difficult%20for%20them%20to%20power%20large%20language%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20within%20languages%20well-served%20by%20large%20language%20models%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1038%2Fs41598-022-06673-y%5C%22%3EEnglish%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fdx.doi.org%2F10.3390%2Fapp14114734%5C%22%3ESpanish%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20your%20experience%20varies%20depending%20on%20which%20dialect%20of%20the%20language%20you%20speak.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERight%20now%2C%20most%20speech%20recognition%20systems%20and%20generative%20AI%20chatbots%20reflect%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.anthropology-news.org%2Farticles%2Fchatgpt-is-reinforcing-your-language-stereotypes%2F%5C%22%3Elinguistic%20biases%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20datasets%20they%20are%20trained%20on.%20They%20echo%20prescriptive%2C%20sometimes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fchatgpt-threatens-language-diversity-more-needs-to-be-done-to-protect-our-differences-in-the-age-of-ai-198878%5C%22%3Eprejudiced%20notions%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20%E2%80%9Ccorrectness%E2%80%9D%20in%20speech.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20AI%20has%20been%20proved%20to%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fsociety%2F2024%2Fdec%2F11%2Fai-tone-shifting-tech-could-flatten-communication-apple-intelligence%5C%22%3Eflatten%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20linguistic%20diversity.%20There%20are%20now%20AI%20startup%20companies%20that%20offer%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftomato.ai%2F%5C%22%3Eerase%20the%20accents%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20their%20users%2C%20drawing%20on%20the%20assumption%20that%20their%20primary%20clientele%20would%20be%20customer%20service%20providers%20with%20call%20centers%20in%20foreign%20countries%20like%20India%20or%20the%20Philippines.%20The%20offering%20perpetuates%20the%20notion%20that%20some%20accents%20are%20less%20valid%20than%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EHuman%20connection%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAI%20will%20presumably%20get%20better%20at%20processing%20language%2C%20accounting%20for%20variables%20like%20accents%2C%20code-switching%20and%20the%20like.%20In%20the%20U.S.%2C%20public%20services%20are%20obligated%20under%20federal%20law%20to%20guarantee%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fcrt%2Ffcs%2FTitleVI%5C%22%3Eequitable%20access%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20services%20regardless%20of%20what%20language%20a%20person%20speaks.%20But%20it%20is%20not%20clear%20whether%20that%20alone%20will%20be%20enough%20incentive%20for%20the%20tech%20industry%20to%20move%20toward%20eliminating%20linguistic%20inequities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20people%20might%20prefer%20to%20talk%20to%20a%20real%20person%20when%20asking%20questions%20about%20a%20bill%20or%20medical%20issue%2C%20or%20at%20least%20to%20have%20the%20ability%20to%20opt%20out%20of%20interacting%20with%20automated%20systems%20when%20seeking%20key%20services.%20That%20is%20not%20to%20say%20that%20miscommunication%20never%20happens%20in%20interpersonal%20communication%2C%20but%20when%20you%20speak%20to%20a%20real%20person%2C%20they%20are%20primed%20to%20be%20a%20sympathetic%20listener.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20AI%2C%20at%20least%20for%20now%2C%20it%20either%20works%20or%20it%20doesn't.%20If%20the%20system%20can%20process%20what%20you%20say%2C%20you%20are%20good%20to%20go.%20If%20it%20cannot%2C%20the%20onus%20is%20on%20you%20to%20make%20yourself%20understood.%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22no-referrer-when-downgrade%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F239281%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Author%3A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22author%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Froberto-rey-agudo-1529250%5C%22%3ERoberto%20Rey%20Agudo%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Research%20Assistant%20Professor%20of%20Spanish%20and%20Portuguese%2C%20Dartmouth%20College)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Disclosure%20Statement%3A%20Roberto%20Rey%20Agudo%20does%20not%20work%20for%2C%20consult%2C%20own%20shares%20in%20or%20receive%20funding%20from%20any%20company