%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b1b8b334-b94d-43ff-896a-cfc24b4d6c31%5C%22%3ESimilar%20blueprints%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20US%20Office%20of%20Personnel%20Management%2C%20which%20is%20sending%20out%20the%20email%20to%20federal%20workers%2C%20vowed%20to%20reward%20top%20performers%20and%20swiftly%20address%20under-performers.%20That%20mirrors%20Musk's%20midnight%20missive%20to%20Twitter%20staff%2C%20which%20demanded%20%26quot%3Bexceptional%20performance%26quot%3B%20as%20the%20%26quot%3Bonly%20passing%20grade%26quot%3B%20and%20presaged%20job%20cuts%20that%20eliminated%20about%2080%25%20of%20the%20company's%20workforce.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOPM%20also%20promised%20a%20leaner%20workforce%2C%20noting%20that%20while%20defense%20and%20security%20agencies%20may%20grow%2C%20most%20federal%20departments%20will%20face%20downsizing%20through%20layoffs%2C%20furloughs%2C%20and%20reclassifying%20roles%20as%20%26quot%3Bat-will%26quot%3B%20employment%2C%20eroding%20civil-service%20protections%20that%20have%20shielded%20workers%20for%20decades.%20Federal%20employees%20must%20also%20meet%20heightened%20standards%20of%20reliability%2C%20loyalty%2C%20and%20trustworthiness%2C%20according%20to%20the%20OPM.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20blueprint%20echoes%20Elon%20Musk's%20rapid-fire%20restructuring%20of%20Twitter.%20Soon%20after%20acquiring%20the%20platform%2C%20Musk%20told%20employees%20they%20had%2040%20hours%20to%20commit%20to%20an%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cem%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3Eextremely%20hardcore%3Cem%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cspan%3E%20work%20environment%20or%20accept%20severance.%20More%20than%206%2C000%20Twitter%20staff%20eventually%20left%20or%20were%20laid%20off%2C%20including%20engineers%20and%20content%20moderators.%20Musk%20also%20issued%20RTO%20mandates.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e59d072d-2aab-4345-ab52-58dec264f828%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ERisks%20and%20rising%20debt%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20risks%20of%20Musk's%20approach%20are%20well-documented.%20Twitter's%20user%20growth%20stalled%20post-takeover%2C%20and%20its%20brand%20reputation%20tanked%20as%20advertisers%20fled%20after%20controversial%20policy%20shifts.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20Trump%2C%20the%20gamble%20is%20potentially%20riskier.%20Twitter%20had%20about%207%2C800%20employees%20pre-Musk%3B%20the%20federal%20government%20employs%20roughly%202.3%20million.%20Mass%20layoffs%20or%20attrition%20could%20destabilize%20everything%20from%20Social%20Security%20processing%20to%20disaster%20response.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYet%20the%20administration%20is%20charging%20ahead%2C%20framing%20the%20overhaul%20as%20an%20effort%20to%20reign%20in%20government%20spending%20and%20control%20the%20national%C2%A0debt.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20Musk%20acquired%20%3Cu%3ETwitter%3C%2Fu%3E%20in%202022%2C%20he%20admitted%20he%20overpaid%20after%20being%20forced%20to%20close%20the%20%2444%20billion%20transaction%20by%20a%20judge.%20It%20was%20a%20highly%20leveraged%20deal%20which%20left%20the%20company%20with%20a%20lot%20of%20debt%20and%20large%20interest%20payments.%20That%20partly%20drove%20Musk's%20drastic%20job%20cuts%20as%20he%20rushed%20to%20save%20money%20and%20prevent%20Twitter%20from%20defaulting.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBy%202023%2C%20he'd%20cut%20more%20than%206%2C000%20employees.%20He%20described%20the%20layoffs%20as%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-laying-off-twitter-was-painful-bbc-spaces-interview-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cu%3Epainful%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bone%20of%20the%20hardest%20things%26quot%3B%20he%20had%20to%20do%20as%20Twitter's%20boss.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20US%20government%20has%20also%20taken%20on%20a%20lot%20of%20debt%20in%20recent%20years.%20While%20no%20one%20expects%20a%20US%20default%20any%20time%20soon%2C%20the%20national%20debt%20has%20soared%20from%20about%20%243.4%20trillion%20in%201980%20to%20more%20than%20%2435%20trillion%20in%202024.%20Roughly%20%2410%20trillion%20in%20debt%20has%20piled%20up%20since%202017%2C%20according%20to%20Treasury%20Department%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffiscaldata.treasury.gov%2Famericas-finance-guide%2Fnational-debt%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cu%3Edata%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERising%20rates%20have%20increased%20the%20cost%20of%20paying%20interest%20on%20this%20massive%20debt%20load.%20In%202023%2C%20these%20annual%20payments%20topped%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fbonds%2Fus-debt-interest-payments-federal-deficit-treasury-bonds-fed-hikes-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cu%3E%241%20trillion%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20stoking%20concern%20among%20some%20economists%20about%20government%20spending.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20partly%20what's%20driving%20the%20Trump%20administration%20to%20try%20to%20make%20the%20US%20government%20more%20efficient.%20Trump%20has%20also%20pledged%20to%20pursue%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-pay-in-taxes-trump-tax-bill-expiring-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cu%3Etax%20cuts%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20putting%20even%20more%20pressure%20on%20his%20administration%20to%20find%20other%20ways%20of%20controlling%20the%20ballooning%20national%20debt.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETrump's%20efficiency%20drive%20has%20already%20caused%20turmoil.%20Some%20government%20workers%20said%20his%20federal%20grant%20freeze%20has%20thrown%20agencies%20into%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%